{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-transaction:4.0.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7087-library-new-request-org.springframework.boot-spring-boot-transaction-4.0.2-f1a67092\n\nThe generated test was created, but the failure appears to be in native-image validation rather than basic test generation. The first Gradle run failed on JVM tests because `TransactionTemplate` and `TransactionalOperator` beans were not created (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-transaction:4.0.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-19T10-25-57-249690Z.log`), but later iterations got past that and repeatedly failed in `:nativeTest` with missing Spring Boot autoconfiguration metadata: `ImportAutoConfigurationImportSelector.class` could not be opened and `OnClassCondition` could not be loaded (`human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-transaction:4.0.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-19T10-30-50-731073Z.log`, also visible in the `10-26-47`, `10-28-50`, and `10-30-26` gradle-test logs). The run metrics still ended as `status: failure` after 4 iterations (`stats/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-transaction/4.0.2/execution-metrics.json`).\n\nThere is also evidence that the missing metadata was fixed locally after the automated run, but not preserved on the branch: `human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-transaction:4.0.2/metadata-fix/codex.log` records uncommitted additions under `metadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-transaction/4.0.2/`, `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-transaction/4.0.2/src/test/resources/`, and a modification to `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-transaction/4.0.2/user-code-filter.json`. After those local changes, reruns passed with `9 tests